// Slot shim required by Buuz135:MultipleHUD (optional dependency).
//
// EndlessLeveling integrates with MultipleHUD via reflection in
// MultipleHudCompatibility.java. When MultipleHUD is installed and we call
// setCustomHud, the MultipleHUD runtime appends THIS document at the
// case-sensitive jar path "Common/UI/Custom/HUD/MultipleHUD.ui" to register
// the slot it renders custom HUDs into. Every mod that participates in the
// MultipleHUD ecosystem ships an identical empty container at this exact
// path.
//
// IMPORTANT: this file is staged outside of src/main/resources because the
// existing mod folder lives at "Common/UI/Custom/Hud/" (capital H, lowercase
// 'ud'). Windows NTFS cannot represent both "Hud/" and "HUD/" as separate
// directories on disk, so we keep the source file here and let shadowJar
// inject it into the jar at the uppercase HUD/ path. See build.gradle.

Group #MultipleHUD {}
